snippet.textDisplay:
AC question of the week
"why does an ant colony need protein?"
In order to lay an egg, the Queen require protein. It's the same reason why a female mosquito sucks blood instead of feeding on nectar like the male counterparts. Protein is sometimes require for the larvae to developed properly and healthily just like how humans require protein in order to grow up without malnutrition kicking in, which the Queen ant might also experience as she's depleting her 'ration' to sustain the colony earlier.

snippet.textDisplay:
“Why does an ant colony need protein?”
Because while sugars are great for the adult workers and their body needs the queen and larvae require it to replace materials lost when the queen creates the eggs, and for the larvae to grow and develop their new bodies.
